President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Julie Elizabeth Hocker of Pennsylvania as an Assistant Secretary of Labor (Disability Employment Policy). Hocker currently serves as the Commissioner of the Administration on Disabilities at the Administration for Community Living at the Department of Health and Human Services. She has previous experience working with the Administration for Children and Families, The Vanguard Group, and the American Conservative Union Foundation. Hocker has a B.A. in economics and political science from St. Mary's College of Maryland and an MBA from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.

President Trump also intends to designate Stefan Charles Passantino of Georgia as the Chairman of the Cultural Property Advisory Committee and Anthony Carroll Wisniewski of Maryland to represent the Cultural Property Collector Category.